SQL> -- =============================================================================
SQL> -- Notes
SQL> -- -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
SQL> -- 1) RESOURCE is deprecated; prefer explicit quotas + least privilege long-term.
SQL> -- 2) CREATE PROCEDURE is the Oracle privilege for procedures, functions, and
SQL> --    packages; there is no separate CREATE PACKAGE / CREATE FUNCTION system grant.
SQL> -- 3) Read-only here = SELECT on tables/views/MVs (and sequences). It does not
SQL> --    grant EXECUTE on application packages in ARGUS_APP / ESM_OWNER. Staging
SQL> --    TCASE_* DDL does not create FKs to ARGUS_APP (avoids REFERENCES privilege).
SQL> -- 4) Object grants require the run-as user to be able to grant on each object
SQL> --    (typically SYS, or schema owners, or GRANT ANY OBJECT PRIVILEGE).
